subject: Update to upstream version 1.8.7
commitMessage:
Update to upstream version 1.8.7

A security vulnerability exists in sudo 1.8.6 which is only addressed by
updating to 1.8.7. The vulnerability allows local users with sudo
permissions to hijack the authorization of another terminal.

This has been assigned CVE-2013-1776

Change-Id: I4d66849d016514cf5f848a0cc9d9bef57c599861
Bug-Tizen: TZPC-4396

comments.message: Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Please add some details to the commit message about why this package upgrade is needed.

Thanks.
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Thanks, Michael.

The last issue I see is a missing git tag for this release (upstream/1.8.7). It should have been autogenerated when you did the gbs import, so just push that tag to the server.

Patch Set 2:

Having problems doing that Patrick it's not allowing a push using --tags, but I do have the upstream/1.8.7 tag locally (Gerrit is prohibiting it)

Patch Set 2:

I tend to just git push origin tag_name though if you can't push tags at all I'd poke somebody on the release engineering team.

Patch Set 2:

Michael, it looks like you're not a maintainer in the Base Domain, so that would explain why you can't push the tag...
Uploaded patch set 3.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

Michael, I pushed the tag and did the necessary rebasing for the tizen branch.  The changes look okay to me.
Patch Set 3: Verified+1
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
